{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, by selecting a group of models from a pool, we can capture the inherent stochasticity in the models while choosing the most accurate ones.",
    "As criteria for the selection of random forest models, we adopted an accuracy measure (Eq. 1) based on the mean absolute percentage error (MAPE; De Myttenaere et al., 2016) and a Monte Carlo cross-validation procedure (Stone, 1974; Kuhn and Johnson, 2013) in which the models were cross-validated on 15 random splits of the phosphorus dataset, using the same ratio of the fitting dataset splitting as in the training phase.",
    "The metric used to evaluate the model's performance in the cross-validation phase was the coefficient of determination (R 2).",
    "The cross-validation provides a measure of the generalization power of each selected model over the fitting dataset.",
    "For each target variable,i.e."
  ]
}